\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. C. cantabrica} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 158 (1753). Pubescent perennial (with many patent hairs at least below) with woody stock and erect herbaceous stems 10-50 cm. Leaves linear to oblanceolate, attenuate at base; basal leaves on each stem widened and scarious at the extreme base. Peduncles terminal and axillary, the lower longer than subtending bracts, 1- to several-flowered. Outer sepals lanceolate to oblanceolate, convex on the back below, cuneate to rounded at base, acute to acuminate. Corolla 15-25 mm, pink. Ovary and capsule pubescent. 2n = 30.{\i  Dry places. S. & S.C. Europe, extending northwards to} c. 48°{\i  N. in E. France and S. Czechoslovakia.} Al Au Bl Bu Co ?Cr Cz Ga Gr Hs Hu It Ju Rm Rs (W, K, E) Sa Si Tu.
