\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. C. humilis} Jacq., {\i Collect. Bot.}{\b  4}: 209 (1791) ({\i C. undulatus} Cav.). Herbaceous annual or short-lived perennial up to 40 cm. Leaves sessile, mostly oblanceolate. Peduncle and pedicel together shorter than or about as long as calyx, 1-flowered. Sepals elliptic-oblong, sparsely pubescent, with scarious margins, mucronulate to acuminate. Corolla 7-12 mm, violet. Capsule pubescent. {\i Dry, open habitats. C. & S. Spain, S.E. Portugal; isolated stations in N.W. Italy and Sicilia.} Hs It Lu Si.
