\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. C. sabatius} Viv.,{\i  Fl. Lib.} 67 (1824). Sparsely to densely pubescent perennial with branched, woody stock; stems 10-50 cm, slender, trailing or ascending, simple or branched, herbaceous. Leaves petiolate; lamina 1-1½(-3) times as long as wide and 3-8 times as long as petiole, orbicular to oblong, cuneate to truncate, entire. Peduncles axillary, usually as long as or shorter than bracts, 1- to 3-flowered. Outer sepals usually acute, inner sepals usually acuminate. Corolla 15-22 mm, pink to blue.{\i  Dry, calcareous rocks. Coasts of N.W. Italy and Sicilia.} It Si. ({\i N.W. Africa.})
