\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. C. arvensis} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 153 (1753). Glabrous or pubescent perennial; stems up to 200 cm, slender, trailing or twining, herbaceous. Leaves petiolate, triangular or ovate-oblong to linear, hastate to sagittate, more or less entire. Peduncles axillary, often about as long as bracts, 1- to 2(3)-flowered. Sepals obtuse to emarginate, and often apiculate. Corolla 10-25 mm, white to pink. Ovary glabrous. 2n = 50. {\i Usually in disturbed habitats. Europe, except the extreme north. }All except Fa Is Sb.
