\pard\f0\fs28 Very variable in pubescence and leaf-shape. Plants with linear to oblong-lanceolate leaves (often with very prominent backwardly-directed auricles) are known as var. linearifolius Choisy. They are native in S. Europe and widely naturalized in the north, and may merit subspecific status.
